                    <h1>Cookie Policy </h1>
                    <p>
                        At Rightous Path, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring that your personal information is handled safely and responsibly. This Cookie Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal data when you visit our website.

                        By using our Website, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.
                    </p>



                    <h3>


                        1. What Are Cookies?

                    </h3>
                    <span class="line-break2"></span>
                    <p>
                        Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device (computer, tablet, mobile phone, etc.) when you visit our Website. They are commonly used to make websites work more efficiently and provide information to the website owners.

                    </p>
                    <span class="line-break2"></span>

                    <h3>

                        2. Types of Cookies We Use


                    </h3>
                    <span class="line-break2"></span>
                    <p>
                        We use the following types of cookies on our Website:

                        Essential Cookies: These cookies are necessary for the basic functionality of the Website. Without these cookies, certain features of the Website may not function correctly (e.g., accessing secure areas, shopping carts).

                        Performance Cookies: These cookies collect information about how visitors use our Website, such as which pages are visited most often. This helps us improve the performance and user experience of our Website.

                        Functionality Cookies: These cookies remember choices you make (such as language preference) to provide a more personalized experience on our Website.

                        Targeting/Advertising Cookies: These cookies are used to deliver relevant ads to you based on your browsing behavior. They also help us measure the effectiveness of our advertising campaigns.

                    </p>
                    <span class="line-break2"></span>

                    <h3>

                        3. How We Use Cookies

                    </h3>
                    <span class="line-break2"></span>
                    <p>
                        We use cookies to:

                        Improve the functionality and performance of our Website.
                        Enhance user experience by remembering your preferences.
                        Analyze trends and track how visitors interact with our Website.
                        Serve relevant advertisements based on your browsing activities.

                    </p>
                    <span class="line-break2"></span>


                    <h3>

                        4. How to Manage Cookies


                    </h3>
                    <span class="line-break2"></span>
                    <p>
                        You have the right to control and manage cookies. You can change your browser settings to block or delete cookies. However, please note that blocking or deleting cookies may impact the functionality and performance of the Website.

                        Here are some options for managing cookies:

                        Browser Settings: Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can set your browser to block all cookies, or to notify you when a cookie is set.
                        Opt-Out: Some third-party cookies, particularly those used for advertising, can be managed by visiting third-party opt-out tools or websites like Network Advertising Initiative or Your Online Choices.
                        For more detailed information on how to adjust your cookie settings, please refer to the help section of your web browser.
                    </p>
                    <span class="line-break2"></span>


                    <h3>

                        5. Third-Party Cookies

